Since this is for understanding the market of internet gaming sites, IGN is not only a gaming website, but also function as something of a, "nerd news" website. They offer previews of various movies, comics, TV shows, etc., so I don&#39;t necessarily have to go BleedingCool, or FilmSchoolRejects, or whatever for information about media that generally appeals to me. <br><BR><font size=1>18:05 08-19-2011</font></TD></TR><TR><td width='4' bgcolor=#CCCCCC>&nbsp;</td><TD ALIGN='LEFT' valign='top' width='70' bgcolor=#CCCCCC><font class="bfont"><B>Patrick M. S </B></font><br><font class="afont"> <A HREF='/magic/resources/buzz.php?ignorename=Patrick M. S '>Ignore</A></font></td><Td valign='top' bgcolor='#CCCCCC' ><font class="bfont">I&#39;d be really interested in your site, man. Please keep me posted. My main draws to go to websites to chit-chat about stuff and learn are video games and movies. <br />
